This is a fix to an issue introduced in https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/pull/2824.

This restores the old behavior of the sprite effect only being applied once at `SpriteBatch.Setup()`.  This makes code like this...

```
spriteBatch.Begin();
effect.CurrentTechnique.Passes [0].Apply();
spriteBatch.Draw(myTexture, new Vector2 (100, 100), Color.White);
spriteBatch.End();
```

... work correctly again.  I verified this fix thru the unit tests which use this technique in several places.

I'm trying to use 

```
            EffectPass pass = effect.CurrentTechnique.Passes[0];
            pass.Apply();
            context.Device.DrawUserPrimitives<VertexPositionColor>(PrimitiveType.LineList, verts, 0, 12);
```

I might totally be doing something wrong, but no matter what I put, nothing seems to show up.

I've looked at the shaders, the matricies, and everything looks  in order, everything else in the scene shows up (Sprite Batched objects, text)  but not the stuff rendered with BasicEffect. Any thoughts?
